14:44.550 --> 14:46.343
Lauren, do you really think
you should be listening?

14:47.469 --> 14:48.512
No.

14:48.596 --> 14:50.306
No, I should be watching, too.

14:52.558 --> 14:54.059
When I met your m..

14:59.732 --> 15:01.191
when I first met your mother

15:01.275 --> 15:04.945
we were both 18
and I didn't know who I was.

15:05.029 --> 15:08.157
'I just knew that I was
in love with this girl.'

15:08.240 --> 15:09.908
And I thank God every day
that I was

15:09.992 --> 15:12.328
'cause she gave me
the greatest gift of my life.

15:13.454 --> 15:15.706
Me.

15:17.041 --> 15:19.293
The greatest two gifts
of my life.

15:21.754 --> 15:25.090
And you know what, this is why

15:25.174 --> 15:29.053
I-I haven't come home
the last couple of years.

15:29.136 --> 15:30.721
I was afraid that you'd hate me.

15:31.847 --> 15:32.765
Hate you?

15:32.848 --> 15:34.099
How could we hate you?

15:34.183 --> 15:35.934
You're everything to us.

15:36.018 --> 15:39.688
Daddy, we don't care
who you're in love with.

15:39.772 --> 15:42.483
Just as long as you're happy.

15:42.566 --> 15:46.111
You have no idea
how much that means to me.

15:46.195 --> 15:48.113
Why can't my daddy be gay?

15:50.574 --> 15:52.159
[sighs]

15:52.242 --> 15:53.327
Ha!

15:53.410 --> 15:55.245
I got to tell you
what a, what a relief it is

15:55.329 --> 15:57.247
to finally be honest with you.

15:57.331 --> 16:00.542
And I promise I will never
keep anything from you again.

16:00.626 --> 16:02.044
This is so nice.

16:03.837 --> 16:06.799
We all love each other,
no matter what.

16:06.882 --> 16:08.926
Like if Val did something
drunk and stupid.

16:10.678 --> 16:14.723
And I did something
that many, many, many

16:14.807 --> 16:16.684
other kids my age do.

16:18.102 --> 16:20.479
We'd all still love
each other, right?

16:20.562 --> 16:22.898
Is there something
that you two want to tell me?

16:25.109 --> 16:26.402
Yes.

16:26.485 --> 16:28.570
Daddy, uh...there's something

16:28.654 --> 16:31.782
I really have been
wanting to get off my chest.

16:31.865 --> 16:34.493
[sighs]

16:34.576 --> 16:36.412
Holly quit college!

16:38.205 --> 16:40.749
Val got drunk and got married!

16:41.500 --> 16:42.710
You're married?

16:42.793 --> 16:44.128
- You got married?
- Yeah, I'm sorry.

16:44.211 --> 16:46.213
It was a huge mistake!
I'm getting it annulled!

16:46.296 --> 16:47.589
Please, don't be
disappointed in me.

16:47.673 --> 16:49.842
And again, Holly quit college!

16:49.925 --> 16:52.803
How could you keep something
like this from me?

16:52.886 --> 16:54.638
Marrying Vic, that's huge!

16:54.722 --> 16:57.599
Whoa, whoa, wait a minute.
How'd you know it was Vic?

16:57.683 --> 16:59.685
Honey, I'm gay, not blind.

17:00.894 --> 17:02.688
And as for you, young lady

17:02.771 --> 17:04.397
we'll talk about this later.

17:04.481 --> 17:07.358
Girls...your new mommy and I
have a great idea.

17:12.114 --> 17:15.242
We have so much to celebrate.
Let's go out and party!

17:15.325 --> 17:16.993
Oh, yes, I love that idea.

17:17.077 --> 17:19.163
I work so hard every day.

17:19.246 --> 17:20.789
Unlike the rest
of my generation

17:20.873 --> 17:23.541
who are partying away
their Dad's money at college.

17:24.752 --> 17:27.253
Not me, daddy.

17:27.337 --> 17:29.882
[piano music]

17:37.097 --> 17:38.766
[applauds]

17:40.350 --> 17:41.310
Hey, you know what?

17:41.393 --> 17:42.394
It's kind of fun being gay.

17:42.478 --> 17:43.479
Oh, come on, you're not

17:43.562 --> 17:44.897
cute enough to be a gay guy.

17:44.980 --> 17:46.648
You are.

17:46.732 --> 17:48.150
[music resumes]

17:48.233 --> 17:50.277
Oh, no, no, no, no.
You know what?

17:50.360 --> 17:53.238
Let's do "Maybe This Time"
from "Cabaret."

17:55.073 --> 17:56.992
Oh, come on, like you don't
all know the words.

17:58.535 --> 17:59.495
And you gave me such a look

17:59.578 --> 18:01.330
when I asked you
to be my sister.

18:04.249 --> 18:06.210
Look at your husband.
How cute is that?

18:06.293 --> 18:08.003
He's such a show-tune queen.

18:09.421 --> 18:11.131
Who knew?

18:11.215 --> 18:12.257
I guess that's what you get

18:12.341 --> 18:14.051
when you marry a guy
after two hours.

18:16.095 --> 18:18.305
Okay, I know it was
a horrible mistake.

18:18.388 --> 18:20.682
I-I mean, how could
I have screwed up so badly?

18:20.766 --> 18:25.437
Now, don't you ever
give yourself a break?

18:25.521 --> 18:29.107
Well, I like to criticize myself
before other people do.

18:29.191 --> 18:32.736
Well maybe if you'd stop,
you'd see that no one else is.

18:33.737 --> 18:37.366
Honey...don't get out of this.

18:37.449 --> 18:40.410
- What?
- Don't end this marriage.

18:40.494 --> 18:41.745
You're in love with him.

18:41.829 --> 18:43.413
Oh, my God!

18:43.497 --> 18:45.165
So not.

18:45.249 --> 18:47.376
Honey...honey!
Look at me.

18:47.459 --> 18:50.712
- Look at me. Look, look, look.
- What?

18:50.796 --> 18:52.673
You're in love with him
and he's in love with you.

18:52.756 --> 18:55.551
I have been watching
the two of you all night.

18:55.634 --> 18:57.761
Oh, please, just 'cause
you're gay, you're suddenly

18:57.845 --> 19:00.055
all intuitive?

19:00.138 --> 19:02.015
We're a very sensitive people.

19:04.309 --> 19:05.727
It also helps
that I'm your father

19:05.811 --> 19:07.813
and I know you
better than anyone.

19:09.773 --> 19:13.151
Now, tell me...what are you
afraid of?

19:15.487 --> 19:17.030
Sharks, bears

19:17.114 --> 19:19.157
leaving the house
with the flatiron on.

19:19.241 --> 19:20.742
Getting your heart broken?

19:21.785 --> 19:23.036
No.

19:27.082 --> 19:28.917
Yes.

19:29.001 --> 19:31.169
I'll tell you what, sweetie.
Get over it.

19:31.253 --> 19:33.172
To be in love
with someone who loves you

19:33.255 --> 19:36.884
and not go for it
just because you're scared..

19:36.967 --> 19:39.720
Oh, trust me

19:39.803 --> 19:41.680
you're gonna miss out
on an awful lot.

19:45.350 --> 19:48.478
Yeah but you haven't had
every guy walk out on you.

19:48.562 --> 19:50.772
Well, did you ever think
that if they didn't

19:50.856 --> 19:52.524
you wouldn't
have ended up with Vic?

19:54.067 --> 19:56.361
When it's the right guy

19:56.445 --> 19:58.447
he won't leave.

19:58.530 --> 20:01.158
[instrumental "Summer Nights"]

20:05.329 --> 20:06.455
All I'm asking you, honey

20:06.538 --> 20:09.041
is to think about it, because..

20:09.124 --> 20:10.876
I love this song,
and I've got to go sing.

20:12.127 --> 20:15.964
♪ Summer lovin' had me a blast ♪

20:16.048 --> 20:20.093
♪ Summer lovin'
happened so fast ♪

